Description: Foot sherd of Attic black-glazed pottery stemless cup; flat base with flaring concave edge below offset wall; glazed black inside and outside, with reserved line at turn of foot; reserved underside; inscription incised on underside.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIV, no. 481)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.2014)
